[SAY] Down three lines to captain. N for next line, P for previous line.
[SAY] So why not just use J and K? Because N means next and P means previous, and that same mnemonic shows up everywhere in Vim. In insert mode, control N and control P cycle through autocomplete suggestions. On the command line, they navigate your command history. J and K don't work in those contexts. Learn the N P pattern now, and it'll pay off later.